recalls.Component: FUEL SYSTEM, GASOLINE:DELIVERY:HOSES, LINES/PIPING, AND FITTINGS
recalls.Summary: THE FUEL HOSE ATTACHED TO THE FUEL DISTRIBUTION RAIL ON THE ENGINE MAY SHRINK BEYOND THE CLAMP FORCE OF THE FUEL HOSE CLAMPS, ALLOWING FUEL TO LEAK.
recalls.Consequence: FUEL LEAKAGE IN THE ENGINE COMPARTMENT CAN CAUSE AN UNDERHOOD FIRE IF THE FUEL COMES IN CONTACT WITH A SOURCE OF IGNITION.
recalls.Remedy: REPLACE THE FUEL HOSE ATTACHED TO THE FUEL RAIL AND INSTALL A NEW SPRING TYPE SELF-TIGHTENING CLAMP.
recalls.Notes: SYSTEM: FUEL LINES.  VEHICLE DESCRIPTION:  PASSENGER CARS.

recalls.Summary: VEHICLE DESCRIPTION:  PASSENGER VEHICLES EQUIPPED WITH VR6 ENGINES.  A COOLANT SYSTEM COMPONENT SUCH AS THE THERMO SWITCH, RADIATOR FAN, OR WATER PUMP, CAN MALFUNCTION CAUSING THE COOLANT TEMPERATURE AND COOLANT SYSTEM PRESSURE TO INCREASE SIGNIFICANTLY.  OVER TIME, EXCESSIVE PRESSURE CAN CAUSE LEAKAGE OF COOLANT FROMTHE SYSTEM, INCLUDING LEAKAGE FROM THE HEAT EXCHANGER.
recalls.Consequence: LEAKAGE OF HOT COOLANT FROM THE HEAT EXCHANGER CAN CAUSE INJURY TO THE FEET OF THE DRIVER OR STEAM UP THE INTERIOR OF THE VEHICLE TEMPORARILY IMPAIRING THE DRIVER'S VISION.
recalls.Remedy: DEALERS WILL INSTALL IN THE COOLANT INLET HOSE TO THE HEATER CORE, A PRESSURE REDUCER WITH A 5MM DIAMETER SECURED BY A SPRING TENSIONED HOSE CLAMP.  ALSO A NEW RELAY THAT WILL CHANGE THE OPERATION OF THE SECONDARY ELECTRICAL COOLANT PUMP WILL BE INSTALLED.  DEALERS WILL ALSO PERFORM A FUNCTIONAL CHECK OF THE COOLING SYSTEM TO MAKE SURE THAT ALL COOLING SYSTEM COMPONENTS OPERATE PROPERLY.
recalls.Notes: OWNER NOTIFICATION BEGAN FEBRUARY 22, 1999.  OWNERS WHO TAKE THEIR VEHICLES TO AN AUTHORIZED DEALER ON AN AGREED UPON SERVICE DATE AND DO NOT RECEIVE THE FREE REMEDY WITHIN A REASONABLE TIME SHOULD CONTACT VWOA AT 1-800-822-8987.    ALSO CONTACT THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION'S AUTO SAFETY HOTLINE AT 1-888-DASH-2-DOT (1-888-327-4236).

recalls.Summary: AN ENGINE COMPARTMENT ELECTRICAL WIRING HARNESS MAY HAVE BEEN ROUTED TOO CLOSE TO A SHEET METAL EDGE. THE WIRING CAN BECOME DAMAGED DURING NORMAL VEHICLE OPERATION DUE TO CHAFING, RESULTING IN AN ELECTRICAL SHORT.
recalls.Consequence: IF A SHORT OCCURS, EITHER THE ENGINE COULD STALL ORTHE RADIATOR FAN COULD STOP OPERATING CAUSING THE ENGINE TO OVERHEAT. EITHERCONDITION COULD RESULT IN A VEHICLE ACCIDENT.
recalls.Remedy: REROUTE AND SECURE VARIOUS WIRING HARNESSES INSIDE THE ENGINE COMPARTMENT.

issues.title: VR6 Engine Chain Tensioner Failure
issues.description: The VR6 engine's chain tensioner can fail, causing the timing chain to jump or break, resulting in catastrophic engine damage including bent valves and piston damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace chain tensioner, timing chain, and inspect/repair any valve damage. Often requires engine rebuild.
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, replace chain tensioner preventively around 80k-100k miles

issues.title: Radiator and Cooling System Failures
issues.description: The plastic radiator end tanks are prone to cracking, and the cooling system components deteriorate causing overheating issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace radiator, water pump, thermostat, and all cooling hoses as a complete system
issues.prevention: Regular coolant flushes, inspect cooling system components annually

issues.title: Spoiler Motor and Mechanism Failure
issues.description: The automatic rear spoiler motor fails or the mechanism becomes jammed, preventing proper spoiler operation.
issues.fix_description: Replace spoiler motor, clean and lubricate mechanism, or install manual spoiler conversion
issues.prevention: Regular operation of spoiler, keep mechanism clean and lubricated

issues.title: Door Handle and Window Regulator Problems
issues.description: Interior and exterior door handles break frequently, and window regulators fail causing windows to drop or bind.
issues.fix_description: Replace door handles with updated parts, replace window regulator mechanisms
issues.prevention: Gentle operation of handles and windows, regular lubrication of window tracks

issues.title: Ignition System Component Failures
issues.description: Ignition coil packs, distributor, and related components fail causing misfires, rough running, and no-start conditions.
issues.fix_description: Replace coil packs, distributor cap, rotor, spark plugs, and ignition wires
issues.prevention: Regular tune-ups, quality ignition components, avoid moisture in distributor

issues.title: Power Steering Pump and Rack Failure
issues.description: Power steering pumps fail and steering racks develop leaks, causing loss of power assist and steering difficulties.
issues.fix_description: Replace power steering pump and/or steering rack, flush system with new fluid
issues.prevention: Regular power steering fluid changes, check for leaks regularly

issues.title: Electrical System and Wiring Issues
issues.description: Various electrical problems including dashboard warning lights, instrument cluster failures, and wiring harness degradation.
issues.fix_description: Diagnose and repair specific electrical faults, replace degraded wiring harnesses
issues.prevention: Keep electrical connections clean and dry, avoid aftermarket electrical modifications

issues.title: Suspension Component Wear
issues.description: Ball joints, tie rod ends, and suspension bushings wear prematurely causing handling issues and tire wear.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn suspension components, perform wheel alignment
issues.prevention: Regular suspension inspections, avoid harsh driving conditions

issues.title: Fuel System Problems
issues.description: Fuel pumps fail and fuel injectors become clogged or leak, causing poor performance and fuel delivery issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump, clean or replace fuel injectors, replace fuel filter
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel, regular fuel filter changes, fuel system cleaning

issues.title: Clutch and Transmission Issues
issues.description: Clutch components wear out and transmission synchros fail, causing shifting difficulties and clutch slippage.
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch kit, repair or rebuild transmission with worn synchros
issues.prevention: Proper shifting technique, avoid riding the clutch, regular transmission fluid changes

editorial.tagline: The narrow-angle VR6 that redefined affordable performance
editorial.hero_blurb: Volkswagen's Corrado VR6 was the sleeper supercar killer that nobody saw coming. With its revolutionary narrow-angle VR6 engine and timeless wedge silhouette, it delivered exotic car performance at a fraction of the price.
editorial.essence: The Corrado VR6 represents Volkswagen's finest hour in performance engineering, combining the silky-smooth power delivery of their revolutionary VR6 engine with sophisticated chassis dynamics. It's the thinking enthusiast's sports car that could embarrass Porsches while offering daily usability.
editorial.heritage: Born from VW's desire to create a halo sports car, the Corrado succeeded the Scirocco in 1988, with the VR6 variant arriving in 1992. It showcased Volkswagen's engineering prowess during their renaissance period, featuring the groundbreaking narrow-angle VR6 engine that would later power everything from GTIs to Audis.
editorial.design_philosophy: Karmann's designers crafted a clean, timeless wedge that prioritized aerodynamics and understated elegance over flashy styling cues. The goal was creating a sophisticated grand tourer that looked fast while standing still, with active rear spoiler deployment adding functional drama.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not a factory racing program, the Corrado VR6 became a grassroots motorsport favorite in touring car racing and time attack events, proving its platform's inherent capability when properly developed by privateers and specialists.
editorial.engine_character: The 2.8L VR6 delivers its power like silk wrapped around steel - smooth, linear, and intoxicating. It builds torque from low revs and pulls cleanly to redline with a creamy urgency that makes every acceleration addictive.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 5-speed manual offers precise, mechanical engagement with satisfying throws and a clutch that provides perfect feedback. Each shift feels deliberate and connected, though the throws are longer than modern sports cars.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Sophisticated multi-link suspension provides excellent body control with a planted, confidence-inspiring feel through corners. The chassis rewards smooth inputs with predictable, neutral handling that flatters both novice and experienced drivers.
editorial.steering_feel: The power-assisted rack delivers excellent on-center feel with progressive weight build-up through corners. It's not overly communicative but provides enough feedback to inspire confidence during spirited driving.
editorial.brake_confidence: Solid, progressive brakes with good initial bite and fade resistance. While not exotic-car powerful, they're more than adequate for the car's performance envelope and provide excellent pedal feel and modulation.
editorial.sound_signature: The VR6's distinctive growl starts as a cultured purr at idle, building to an intoxicating mechanical symphony under load. The narrow-angle configuration creates a unique harmonic that's neither inline-six smooth nor V6 raspy - it's purely VR6.
editorial.ideal_owner: The sophisticated enthusiast who values understated performance, engineering excellence, and daily usability over raw numbers or badge prestige. Perfect for someone who appreciates mechanical refinement and timeless design.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Those seeking maximum performance per dollar, anyone requiring extensive rear seating, or enthusiasts who prefer raw, unfiltered driving experiences over refined touring capability.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for well-maintained examples with comprehensive service records, as the VR6 engine and electrical systems require proper care. Values are rising steadily as enthusiasts recognize the Corrado's significance in automotive history.
pros: Timeless, elegant design that ages gracefully
Silky-smooth VR6 engine with intoxicating sound
Sophisticated chassis with excellent road manners
cons: Complex electrical systems prone to gremlins
Limited rear seat space and practicality
